{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"850576ce-14db-491c-bd93-98ded9418568","content":"\n\nIn .NET 10 MAUI, the iOS-specific `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` was replaced with a **cross-platform** `SafeAreaRegions` property on `Page`.\n\n**Before (.NET 9):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\n**After (.NET 10):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage SafeAreaRegions=\"All\">\n```\n\n`SafeAreaRegions` is a flags enum — you can also target specific edges:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Only top and bottom -->\n<ContentPage SafeAreaRegions=\"Top,Bottom\">\n```\n\nAvailable values: `None`, `All`, `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, `Right`.\n\nYou can drop the `xmlns:ios` namespace declaration if it was only used for `UseSafeArea`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a7dde5c-1435-4c78-8c1a-b20aa6a39294","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI migration issue from .NET 9 to .NET 10 regarding safe area handling on iOS. This is a knowledge question about a framework change.\n\nIn .NET 10 (which would be a preview/RC as of April 2026), Microsoft made changes to how safe area insets are handled in MAUI for iOS. Let me think about what I know:\n\nIn .NET MAUI for .NET 9 and earlier, you could use the iOS platform-specific `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` to automatically pad content away from the status bar, notch, and home indicator areas.\n\nIn .NET 10, Microsoft deprecated or changed this approach. \n\nThe new approach uses a cross-platform `SafeAreaRegions` property on `Page` instead of the old iOS-specific `UseSafeArea` attribute, which was part of a broader effort to standardize safe area handling across different platforms. I'm confident about this change in .NET 10 MAUI — the new `SafeAreaRegions` property replaces the old iOS-specific `UseSafeArea` approach, giving you a cross-platform way to control which safe area regions the page respects using a flags enum.","outputTokens":939},"id":"809b5b25-c752-48bc-b237-06e80ec0297a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:06:56.414Z","parentId":"85d23d7f-50f5-42a6-9efb-521b51442b2e"}
